				<div class="postbody">
				If you give me links to some high end pc hardware to build a studio-ready PC for under 3,000 dollars I'll love you forever! (yes PC, not a mac).
<br />

<br />
Im only half serious, I saw your thread on bic's question and wondered if you could give me ideas for my up and coming studio pc.  Looking for a graphics card with a Dual Video Input, as well as a nice professional quality sound card.  I assume I'll need a dual processor setup as well as a raid hd setup for speed / efficiency.  I don't know if audio editing is really your field, but I could go for some suggestions.
<br />

<br />
I guess my goal in the long run is a pc I can upgrade to protools hardware/software when I have the $, but still make use of some studio equipment (like a triton keyboard  / dedicated sampler / soundboard) with all the software I already have.  (Cubase SX, Acid 4.0, Reason 2.5, etc)<br />
