			<tr><td colspan="2"><hr /></td></tr>
			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				I'm currently running Steinberg VST (24-bit, 32 tracks) recording software with a Tascam USB digital mixer w/ a pair of Yamaha NS10s on a PIII 2Ghz 768GB RAM and it runs fine. I initially tried using my soundcard, but it just doesn't sound right and your mix never turns out like you want to. As for hardware, look for a high Front-side Bus (FSB) speed, lots of RAM and a fast hard-drive. Don't even bother with RAID 1-5 because it's not going to be within your price range and it will ultimately slow down data transfer rates which could cause your tracks to stutter (very annoying). If you're serious about recording, then a set of quality studio speakers should be at the top of your list as well.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
		</table>
		</td>
	</tr>
