				<div class="postbody">
				</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> Don't even bother with RAID 1-5 because it's not going to be within your price range and it will ultimately slow down data transfer rates which could cause your tracks to stutter (very annoying). </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Only true if you use SCSI hardware.
<br />

<br />
Nearly every motherboard out there comes with Serial ATA ports now. The smart thing to do is buy 3-4 SATA drives and raid them with the onboard tech. You get far faster transfer and access times than you can get with any single drive configuration. It costs nothing; you're already paying for it when you buy any new mobo.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
		</table>
		</td>
